# CSS standards

Full checklist: `docs/static-site-standards.md` (CSS, theming, fonts).

## Constraints

- No preprocessor. Use custom properties for design tokens (light/dark via `prefers-color-scheme` + optional `[data-theme]`).

## Layout & responsive

- Flexbox / Grid / Subgrid; `gap`; `aspect-ratio`
- Container queries (`@container`) where components need it
- Logical properties: `margin-inline`, `padding-block`, etc.
- Fluid type/spacing: `clamp()`, `min()`, `max()`

## Selectors & interaction

- `:has()`, `:is()`, `:where()`, `:not()`; nesting with `&`
- `:focus-visible`, `:focus-within` — visible focus rings (a11y)
- `@layer` for reset → tokens → components → utilities

## Motion & effects

- Respect `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disable or shorten animations
- `prefers-contrast`, `prefers-color-scheme`
- View Transitions API when enhancing navigation
- `scroll-snap`, `scroll-behavior`, `backdrop-filter`, `content-visibility` as needed
- Color: `oklch()` / `lch()` / `color-mix()` where supported

## Print

- `@media print` rules for key pages when applicable

## Fonts

- Never `@import` Google Fonts — load via `<link>` in HTML (see fonts-icons rule)
- `font-display: swap` on `@font-face` if self-hosting
